+## Maintaining this fork
+
+This fork uses `origin/main` as the branch I install from my Neovim configuration. The branch is periodically rebased on top of `upstream/main`, then my local patch stack is re-applied.
+
+Current upstream remote:
+
+```bash
+git remote add upstream https://github.com/esmuellert/codediff.nvim.git
+```
+
+Refresh the local view of both repositories:
+
+```bash
+git fetch upstream origin
+```
+
+Rebuild this fork's `main` branch from upstream and apply the maintained patches:
+
+```bash
+git switch main
+git reset --hard upstream/main
+
+git cherry-pick origin/feat/history-auto-expand-commits
+git cherry-pick origin/feat/compact-mode
+git cherry-pick origin/feat/inline-diff-api
+
+git push --force-with-lease origin main
+```
+
+For later upstream syncs, rebase this fork's `main` on upstream:
+
+```bash
+git fetch upstream origin
+git switch main
+git rebase upstream/main
+git push --force-with-lease origin main
+```
+
+Enable Git's conflict-resolution reuse to make repeated rebases easier:
+
+```bash
+git config rerere.enabled true
+```
+
+When adding a new maintained change, commit it first and then regenerate the patch export:
+
+```bash
+git add README.md
+git commit -m "docs: document maintained fork workflow"
+
+mkdir -p patches
+git format-patch upstream/main..main -o patches
+```
+
+The Git commits on `main` are the source of truth. Files in `patches/` are an exported backup/documentation artifact that can be re-applied with:
+
+```bash
+git am -3 patches/*.patch
+```
+
